<%- include("../../partials/header") %> <%- include("../../partials/navbar") %>
<%- include("../../partials/message") %>

<div class="bg-gray-100">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto py-8 px-4">
    <!-- Thumbnail -->
    <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-lg">
      <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/800x400" alt="Blog Thumbnail" class="w-full h-auto object-cover">
    </div>

    <!-- Title -->
    <h1 class="mt-6 text-4xl font-bold text-gray-800 leading-tight">
      How to Build a Modern Blog Using MongoDB, Express, and Node.js
    </h1>

    <!-- Metadata -->
    <div class="flex items-center mt-4 space-x-4 text-gray-500 text-sm">
      <div class="flex items-center space-x-2">
        <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/40" alt="Author" class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full">
        <span>John Doe</span>
      </div>
      <span>·</span>
      <span>5 min read</span>
      <span>·</span>
      <span>December 23, 2024</span>
    </div>

    <!-- Tags -->
    <div class="mt-4 flex space-x-2">
      <span class="bg-blue-100 text-blue-600 text-xs font-medium px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Node.js</span>
      <span class="bg-green-100 text-green-600 text-xs font-medium px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Express</span>
      <span class="bg-gray-100 text-gray-600 text-xs font-medium px-3 py-1 rounded-full">MongoDB</span>
    </div>

    <!-- Content -->
    <div class="mt-6 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        Building a modern blog is an exciting journey that involves utilizing the latest technologies. In this guide, we will walk you through creating a complete blog application using MongoDB for the database, Express as the backend framework, and Node.js for the server runtime.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4">
        The goal of this project is to create a seamless reading experience while ensuring developers enjoy the ease of integrating these tools together. Let’s dive in!
      </p>
      <blockquote class="mt-6 border-l-4 border-gray-300 pl-4 italic text-gray-600">
        "The beauty of building a blog is that it’s both challenging and rewarding."
      </blockquote>
      <p class="mt-4">
        To get started, make sure you have Node.js installed. Then, create a new project directory and initialize a new npm package. Once set up, install the required dependencies like Express and Mongoose.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Like/Dislike Buttons -->
    <div class="mt-8 flex items-center space-x-4">
      <button class="flex items-center text-gray-600 hover:text-green-500">
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-5 h-5 mr-1" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M14 9l-5 5m0 0l-5-5m5 5V3" />
        </svg>
        <span>123 Likes</span>
      </button>
      <button class="flex items-center text-gray-600 hover:text-red-500">
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-5 h-5 mr-1" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10 15l5-5m0 0l5 5m-5-5v12" />
        </svg>
        <span>12 Dislikes</span>
      </button>
    </div>

    <!-- Comments Section -->
    <div class="mt-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800">Comments (3)</h2>
      <div class="mt-4 space-y-6">
        <!-- Comment 1 -->
        <div class="flex space-x-4">
          <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/40" alt="User" class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full">
          <div>
            <p class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-800">Jane Smith</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-1">Great post! Very informative.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <!-- Comment 2 -->
        <div class="flex space-x-4">
          <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/40" alt="User" class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full">
          <div>
            <p class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-800">Mike Johnson</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-1">Looking forward to the next article!</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

